#School
This is an 18+ game that is based around being a student going to school. It offers diverse cheat codes. I have yet to even run the game but in the game files, after having ran unrpa on archive.rpa, we get the joys of opening multiple files. It's nice of the creator, "Kaito", to have clearly labeled, (not encrypted), the cheat codes that he wants people to use, but he also forgot to encrypt the patreon codes, which happen to be the same codes from GTA San andreas. Thanks dude. To access the menu there seems to be a check of like if you are part of patreon, doesn't seem as though it even works, but it does have a little loophole, where changing the if condition to either True, or False, depending on the context, this check is easily bypassed. These game files feel as if there was an attempt to be secretive but they gave up half way through. They should have probably instead tried to atleast hash the codes themselves, as the format is sometimes something like Patreon_code_123456_xxxxxx, where the x's are a random hexidecimal code not following any type of encryption, so good on them I guess if that was how it was stored. But it needs work.
